@* THE PRECEDENCE WITNESS THAT ACTUALLY BITES, and it exists because the obvious one does not.

   `/item/new` against `/item/{Id:int}` looks like a precedence test and is not: ':int' REJECTS "new", so
   the scan reaches the literal page whatever order the table is in. Neutralising the sort left the
   contract green, which is how that was found.

   This pair has no such escape. `/tag/{Slug}` is a BARE parameter, so it matches "all" perfectly well;
   the only thing that sends /tag/all here rather than there is that a literal segment outranks a
   parameter. Blazor picks this page, and it picks it regardless of declaration order. *@
